Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Chop artichoke hearts in a food processor. Add 2 cups Parmesan, mayonnaise, garlic, lemon zest and cayenne; puree until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Place in two gratin or shallow baking dishes (2-cup capacity). Sprinkle each dish with 1 tablespoon Parmesan. Bake the dip until golden on top and heated through, 10 to 20 minutes.